(85, 'Data Analysis & Reporting Techniques Using Excel', 2700, '2022-09-03', '2022-09-24', '10:00:00', '15:00:00', 100, 'images/courses/1644685124.png', 14, 0, '2022-08-21 06:19:22', '2022-02-12 16:58:45', '<p>Overview<br />&bull; It is no surprise for corporate staff to be staff to be overwhelmed by the<br />abundance of instructed data.</p>\r\n<p>&bull; ERPs and database have evolved to a point where they can house<br />amazingly large amounts of data the question now is, what do you do<br />with this data to add value .</p>\r\n<p>&bull; this workshop will introduce business intelligence (BI), hands on, to<br />allow you to clean, normalize, interpret, analyze and report large volumes<br />of data. you will be able to establish historical relationships, analyze the<br />current situation and predict future strategies .</p>\r\n<p>Learning Outcomes :&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&bull; Design detailed reports from multiple sets of data through a variety of sources.<br />&bull; Manipulate the data within your reports to suit your business needs.<br />&bull; Extract data from your reports to use in different functions and formulas.<br />&bull; Create an attractive chart and diagram for your business reports to help illustrate data<br />&bull; Learn the concepts of gathering, cleaning and storage of data.<br />&bull; Come up with multiple scenarios to resolve business problems within extracted data.<br />&bull; Design a data model for your large data groups.<br />&bull; Mine and uncover hidden information with DAX.<br />&bull; Use Power Queries and practice shaping, blending and exploring files in Excel`s.<br />query editor , and create completely automated loading procedures inside of Excel.<br />&bull; Use Power Pivot and DAX to explore and analyze our Excel data model.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you want full outlines contact us on the below numbers :&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>T:</strong>&nbsp;<a href=\"tel:(202)%2025281172\">(202) 25281172</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>M:</strong>&nbs